<! [CDATA[
 Nescafé Logo
Nescafé is a brand of coffee made by Nestlé. It comes in many different forms. The name is a portmanteau of the words “Nestlé” and “café”. Nestlé first introduced their flagship coffee brand in Switzerland on 1 April 1938. Source Nescafé is one of the brands that incline toward advancement to upheaval. Once they made their logo in 1938, the organization was refining and altering it consistently, with no emotional changes and developments.
